        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_UsersInRoles_GetUsersInRoles",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve a list of users who are associated with a specific role within a given application. It operates within the context of an ASP.NET membership schema, which typically involves tables like "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_Applications",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_Roles",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_Users",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_UsersInRoles",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". The procedure takes an application name and a role name as input, identifies the corresponding application and role IDs, and then fetches the usernames of users assigned to that role within the specified application."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
